          .item
            %h2 Reddit redesign concept
            .tags UX, UI <span class="lower">as an independent project</span>
            %p
              I love reddit. The content, not the site. I find myself on Imgur browsing reddit content all the time. This seemed like a red flag for their interface, so I redesigned it: <a href="https://medium.com/@stothelios/reddit-redesign-concept-913aa552124e">Read about the entire process on Medium</a>
            %h3
              %i.margin-right.fa.fa-thumbs-o-down
              The problem(s)
            %p
              <strong>The main problem is the flow.</strong> Users have to revisit the homepage after clicking on each link. That’s a lot of clicking back and forth.
            %p
              <strong>There are also issues with the UI.</strong> The homepage is full of items competing for attention and it’s hard to preview images with the small existing thumbnails.
            %h3
              %i.margin-right.fa.fa-lightbulb-o
              The solution

